# Workflow

Follow this order for every task.

## Before Coding

1. Read [docs/SYSTEM_MAP.md](../../docs/SYSTEM_MAP.md) to locate the relevant system.
2. Read the matching `docs/systems/<name>.md` for design rules and public API.
3. Read [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) if crossing system boundaries.
4. Identify affected systems. Minimize side effects.
5. State any assumptions you had to make.

## While Coding

- Implement ONE feature at a time.
- Keep changes focused - do not "improve" unrelated code.
- Prefer extending existing architecture over rewriting it.
- Never guess. If unclear, stop and ask.

## After Coding

- Check for regressions in adjacent systems.
- Keep naming consistent with [docs/AI_RULES.md](../../docs/AI_RULES.md) conventions.
- Do not break existing public APIs.
- Update [docs/PROGRESS.md](../../docs/PROGRESS.md) and the relevant `docs/systems/<name>.md` (see `80-docs-sync.mdc`).

## When Unsure

- Never guess.
- Ask questions.
- State assumptions explicitly.
- Offer alternatives with trade-offs.

## When Refactoring Is Recommended

- Never rewrite working systems unless explicitly requested.
- If refactoring is needed: explain why, describe risks, wait for approval.
